 collegiate institution are classified as new freshman and must meet the entrance requirements to the College that are specified for new freshmen  The College of Engineering recommends that each new freshman complete a strong high school mathematics curriculum that includes algebra  geometry  and trigonometry  The College will give admission priority to residents of the State of Illinois  Applicants who are not residents of the State of Illinois may be admitted only after review by the College Request Admissions Information  You may request undergraduate admissions information on line  through UIC  s Office of Admissions and Records  Select "Engineering" as your choice of Programs  For more specific information regarding the ECE Undergraduate Program or if you have any questions  please contact the Student Affairs Office at               or                             fax  or send e mail to ugrad info uic ece edu Apply now GETTING STARTED Undergraduate Admissions Undergraduate Catalog  Information and Objectives  Information and Objectives  Frequently Asked Questions Frequently Asked Questions DEGREE REQUIREMENTS BS in Electrical Engineering Undergraduate Catalog Undergraduate Catalog Curriculum  Curriculum  Curriculum  Curriculum  BS in Computer Engineering Undergraduate Catalog Undergraduate Catalog Curriculum  Curriculum  Curriculum  Curriculum  BS in Engineering Physics Undergraduate Catalog Undergraduate Catalog Curriculum  Curriculum  Curriculum  Curriculum  SPECIAL PROGRAMS Honors College Honors College Guaranteed Professional Program Admission  GPPA Guaranteed Professional Program Admission  GPPA Guaranteed Paid Internship Program Guaranteed Paid Internship Program UNDERGRADUATE FORMS Change of Major Modification of Major Prerequisite Petition Prerequisite Petition Proposal for Undergraduate Research Proposal for Undergraduate Research Undergraduate Student General Petition Undergraduate Student General Petition Intercollege Transfer Petition Intercollege Tr